{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月十五|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 15일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 15''' is the 15th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ) – [[:en:Battle of Sekigahara|Battle of Sekigahara]] . Leads to the deaths of many people listed in [[#Deaths]] * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 18 (Gregorian [[:en:1613|1613]] [[:en:October 28|October 28]] ) – [[:en:Hasekura Tsunenaga|Hasekura Tsunenaga]] and the {{ill|Keichō Embassy|ja|Keichō遣欧使節|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō Embassy|qq=}} from [[:en:Sendai Domain|Sendai Domain]] depart from Japan. * {{ill|Enkyō|ja|Enkyō|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enkyō|qq=}} 4 (Gregorian [[:en:1747|1747]] [[:en:October 18|October 18]] ) – [[:en:Tanuma Okitsugu|Tanuma Okitsugu]] is appointed {{ill|Koshōgumi|ja|小姓組|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koshōgumi|qq=}} commander. * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 6 (Gregorian [[:en:1853|1853]] [[:en:October 17|October 17]] ) – The {{ill|Ban on Large Shipbuilding|ja|大船建造の禁|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ban on Large Shipbuilding|qq=}} is lifted, allowing large ship construction for the first time in approximately 250 years.
== Births == * {{ill|Ken’ei|ja|建炎|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ken’ei|qq=}} 4 ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1130|1130]] [[:en:October 18|October 18]] ) – {{ill|Zhu Xi|ja|朱子|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhu Xi|qq=}} , founder of [[:en:Cheng–Zhu school|Neo-Confucianism]] (+ [[:en:1200|1200]] ). * [[:en:Jōkyō|Jōkyō]] 2 (Gregorian [[:en:1685|1685]] [[:en:October 12|October 12]] ) – [[:en:Ishida Baigan|Ishida Baigan]] , philosopher (+ [[:en:1744|1744]] ). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei|qq=}} 8 (Gregorian [[:en:1796|1796]] [[:en:October 15|October 15]] ) – [[:en:Date Narimune|Date Narimune]] , 10th lord of [[:en:Sendai Domain|Sendai Domain]] (+ [[:en:1819|1819]] ). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 8 (Gregorian [[:en:1825|1825]] [[:en:October 26|October 26]] ) – [[:en:Iwakura Tomomi|Iwakura Tomomi]] , politician and key figure of the [[:en:Meiji Restoration|Meiji Restoration]] (+ [[:en:1883|1883]] ). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1 (Gregorian [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:October 30|October 30]] ) – [[:en:Fusakichi Omori|Ōmori Fusakichi]] , geoscientist (+ [[:en:1923|1923]] ).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Hōen|Hōen]] 6 (Julian [[:en:1140|1140]] [[:en:October 27|October 27]] ) – [[:en:Toba Sōjō|Kakuyū]] , also known as {{ill|Toba Sōjō|ja|鳥羽Monk正覚猷|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toba Sōjō|qq=}} , high-Ranking monk of the [[:en:Tiantai|Tendai school]] and purported creator of the [[:en:Chōjū-jinbutsu-giga|Chōjū-jinbutsu-giga]] . * [[:en:Kagen|Kagen]] 3 (Julian [[:en:1305|1305]] [[:en:October 4|October 4]] ) – [[:en:Emperor Kameyama|Emperor Kameyama]] , 90th Emperor of Japan (* [[:en:1249|1249]] ). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 7 (Julian [[:en:1579|1579]] [[:en:October 5|October 5]] ) – [[:en:Matsudaira Nobuyasu|Matsudaira Nobuyasu]] , eldest son of [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]] (* [[:en:1559|1559]] ). * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ) – [[:en:Ōtani Yoshitsugu|Ōtani Yoshitsugu]] , military commander. * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ) – {{ill|Hiratsuka Tamehiro|ja|平塚為広|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hiratsuka Tamehiro|qq=}} , military commander. * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ) – [[:en:Shima Sakon|Shima Kiyooki]] , military commander. * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ) – [[:en:Toda Katsushige|Toda Katsunari]] , military commander. * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ) – {{ill|Kimotsuki Kanemori|ja|肝付兼護|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kimotsuki Kanemori|qq=}} , military commander (* [[:en:1561|1561]] ). * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ) – [[:en:Shimazu Toyohisa|Shimazu Toyohisa]] , military commander (* [[:en:1570|1570]] ).
